  "prompt": "Can I use Google analytics on evaluating various company's websites without actually being owner of those websites?",
  "response": "No, you cannot use Google Analytics to evaluate websites you do not own or have explicit permission to access. Google Analytics requires you to add a unique tracking code to the website's pages, which is something only the website owner or someone with administrative access can do. Using Google Analytics without authorization would violate Google's terms of service and could potentially be illegal, depending on the jurisdiction and circumstances. If you need analytics data for a website you do not own, consider contacting the website owner directly to request access or for them to share the data with you.",
